### Elemental Beauty — API test file (REST Client extension)
### After login/register, copy the token into @token below.
### Roles: member < officer < treasurer < admin
### First admin (one-time, from terminal):
###   docker exec -it elemental-db psql -U postgres -d elemental -c "UPDATE members SET role = 'admin' WHERE user_id = 1;"

@base = http://localhost:5003
@token = PASTE_TOKEN_HERE

### ---------- auth (public) ----------

### Register a new user
POST {{base}}/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "username": "rachel",
    "email": "rachel@example.com",
    "password": "test1234"
}

### Login
POST {{base}}/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "username": "rachel",
    "password": "test1234"
}

### Verify email with the emailed token (no login needed — in dev the token
### comes back in the register response / server console)
POST {{base}}/auth/verify-email
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "verificationToken": "PASTE_VERIFICATION_TOKEN_HERE"
}

### Re-send the verification email (logged-in users whose token expired)
POST {{base}}/auth/resend-verification
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### Sign waiver (second flip creates the members row)
POST {{base}}/auth/waiver
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### Forgot password (dev mode returns the resetToken; later it gets emailed)
POST {{base}}/auth/forgot-password
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "email": "rachel@example.com"
}

### Reset password (token is single-use and expires in 15 min)
POST {{base}}/auth/reset-password
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "resetToken": "PASTE_RESET_TOKEN_HERE",
    "newPassword": "mynewpassword"
}

### ---------- members (member+) ----------

### Roster
GET {{base}}/members
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### My profile
GET {{base}}/members/me
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### My QR code (PNG)
GET {{base}}/members/me/qr
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### Update my profile
PUT {{base}}/members/me
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "instagram": "@rachel.makes.balms"
}

### Award social-media points (officer+): instagram_repost +1, instagram_follow +2, discord_join +2
### (attendance points are automatic at check-in/admission and can't be granted here)
POST {{base}}/members/2/points
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "action": "instagram_follow"
}

### Change a member's role (admin only)
PUT {{base}}/members/2/role
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "role": "officer"
}

### Delete my account
DELETE {{base}}/members/me
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### ---------- labs (member+; writes officer+) ----------

### List labs (?when=upcoming or ?when=past)
GET {{base}}/labs?when=upcoming
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### Lab detail (preview until quiz passed; full for officer+)
GET {{base}}/labs/1
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### Create lab (officer+)
POST {{base}}/labs
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "title": "Lip Balm Formulation",
    "date": "2026-09-15",
    "description": "Intro to anhydrous balms",
    "ingredients": "Beeswax, shea butter, jojoba oil",
    "capacity": 20
}

### Update lab (officer+)
PUT {{base}}/labs/1
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "safetyNote": "Hot wax — heat gloves required"
}

### Add a lesson (officer+)
POST {{base}}/labs/1/lessons
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "title": "Why anhydrous products resist microbes",
    "explanation": "No water activity means no microbial growth..."
}

### Add a quiz question with options (officer+)
POST {{base}}/labs/1/quiz
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "question": "Which ingredient hardens the balm?",
    "options": [
        { "answerText": "Beeswax", "isCorrect": true },
        { "answerText": "Jojoba oil", "isCorrect": false },
        { "answerText": "Fragrance", "isCorrect": false }
    ]
}

### RSVP (auto-waitlists when the lab is full)
POST {{base}}/labs/1/rsvp
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### Un-RSVP (auto-promotes the oldest waitlisted member)
DELETE {{base}}/labs/1/rsvp
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### Check in a scanned member (officer+; qrToken comes from the member's QR)
POST {{base}}/labs/1/checkin
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "qrToken": "PASTE_SCANNED_QR_TOKEN_HERE"
}

### Admit waitlist into no-show seats, oldest first (officer+)
POST {{base}}/labs/1/admit-waitlist
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### Submit quiz answers — { questionId: [optionIds] }; 100% required to pass
POST {{base}}/labs/1/quiz/submit
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "answers": {
        "1": [1]
    }
}

### ---------- events (member+; writes officer+) ----------

### List events (?when=upcoming|past, ?type=official|social — combinable)
GET {{base}}/events?when=upcoming&type=social
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### Create event (officer+). type is required: official (+5 pts) or social (+3 pts).
### capacity is optional — omit for unlimited; set it to get lab-style waitlisting.
POST {{base}}/events
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "title": "Fall Kickoff Social",
    "type": "social",
    "date": "2026-08-30",
    "description": "Meet the club!",
    "capacity": 50
}

### RSVP / un-RSVP
POST {{base}}/events/1/rsvp
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

###
DELETE {{base}}/events/1/rsvp
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### Check in (officer+)
POST {{base}}/events/1/checkin
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "qrToken": "PASTE_SCANNED_QR_TOKEN_HERE"
}

### Admit entire event waitlist (officer+)
POST {{base}}/events/1/admit-waitlist
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### ---------- reimbursements (officer+; decisions treasurer+) ----------

### Submit a request (always created pending)
POST {{base}}/reimbursements
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "explanation": "Beeswax and shea butter",
    "amountRequested": 42.50,
    "category": "supplies"
}

### My history
GET {{base}}/reimbursements/mine
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### Review queue (treasurer+)
GET {{base}}/reimbursements?status=pending
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### Approve (treasurer+) — the DB trigger auto-creates the ledger expense
PUT {{base}}/reimbursements/1/status
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "status": "approved"
}

### Deny (treasurer+) — denialExplanation required
PUT {{base}}/reimbursements/2/status
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "status": "denied",
    "denialExplanation": "No receipt attached"
}

### ---------- transactions (officer+ reads; treasurer+ writes) ----------

### Ledger (?type=&category=&from=&to=)
GET {{base}}/transactions
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### Analytics summary
GET {{base}}/transactions/summary
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### CSV export
GET {{base}}/transactions/export
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### Record a manual entry (treasurer+)
POST {{base}}/transactions
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "type": "income",
    "source": "Fall membership dues",
    "amount": 300,
    "category": "membership_dues"
}

